You are working on branch `frank/fix-subcategory-duplicates` in the catalog project.

## Bug Description
The uniqueness constraint for subcategories is bypassed during the update flow. While creation correctly blocks duplicates, the edit/update logic fails to validate them. This allows saving categories with duplicate subcategory names through the PUT /catalog/v1/categories endpoint.

## Current Changes (already staged but not committed)
The following changes have been made to fix this bug:

### CategoryService.cs
1. Added `HasDuplicateChildrenNames` check in the `UpdateCategories` method (after `PrepareCategoriesTree`, before flattening):
```csharp
if (HasDuplicateChildrenNames(categories))
{
    NotifyError("Não é permitido cadastrar subcategorias com nomes duplicados");
    return;
}
```

2. Added the `HasDuplicateChildrenNames` private static method that flattens the category tree and checks for duplicate names (case-insensitive):
```csharp
private static bool HasDuplicateChildrenNames(IEnumerable<CategoryDto> categories)
{
    foreach (var category in categories)
    {
        var allNamesInTree = FlattenCategoryDtoTree(new[] { category })
            .Select(c => c.Name)
            .ToList();

        if (allNamesInTree
            .GroupBy(n => n, StringComparer.OrdinalIgnoreCase)
            .Any(g => g.Count() > 1))
            return true;
    }

    return false;
}
```

### CategoryServiceTests.cs
Added a test `ShouldReturnErrorWhenUpdatingCategoryWithDuplicateChildrenNames` that creates a category with duplicate "teste" names at different levels and verifies the error notification.

## Your Task
1. Read the current files to verify the implementation is correct
2. Verify the test is properly structured and will pass
3. Run the tests to confirm everything works: `dotnet test JSM.Catalog.Test/JSM.Catalog.Test.csproj --filter "CategoryServiceTests" --no-restore`
4. If there are any issues, fix them. If everything is good, confirm the implementation is complete.

Important: The changes are already in the working directory (unstaged). Do NOT create new files. Only fix issues if found.
